🚀 JPA Relationships kya hote hain?

👉 Jab tables ek dusre se connected hote hain
User → Orders

👉 Ek user ke multiple orders ho sakte hain

🧠 Simple Samajh
Relationship = tables ke beech connection

🔥 Types of Relationships
1️. OneToOne
👉 Ek user → ek profile

@OneToOne
private Profile profile;


2️. OneToMany
👉 Ek user → multiple orders

@OneToMany(mappedBy = "user")
private List<Order> orders;


3️. ManyToOne
👉 Multiple orders → ek user

@ManyToOne
@JoinColumn(name = "user_id")
private User user;


4️. ManyToMany
👉 Students ↔ Courses

@ManyToMany
private List<Course> courses;


🔥 MOST IMPORTANT (Real Example)

🧩 User Entity
@Entity
public class User {

    @Id
    @GeneratedValue
    private Long id;

    private String name;

    @OneToMany(mappedBy = "user")
    private List<Order> orders;
}

🧩 Order Entity
@Entity
public class Order {

    @Id
    @GeneratedValue
    private Long id;

    private String product;

    @ManyToOne
    @JoinColumn(name = "user_id")
    private User user;
}

🧠 Samajh kya hua?
👉 DB me:

- User table
id | name

- Order table
id | product | user_id

👉 user_id = foreign key

⚡ mappedBy kya hota hai?
@OneToMany(mappedBy = "user")

👉 Bol raha:
“Relation Order class me defined hai”

🔥 Important Concept (OWNING SIDE)
👉 @ManyToOne side = owner
👉 wahi decide karta hai:

foreign key kaha banegi
🧠 Flow Samajh

User → orders list
Order → user reference

⚡ Save Example
User user = new User();
user.setName("Pulkit");

Order order = new Order();
order.setProduct("Laptop");
order.setUser(user);

userRepository.save(user);
orderRepository.save(order);


🔥 Fetch Example
User user = userRepository.findById(1L).get();
System.out.println(user.getOrders());

⚠️ Common Problems
👉 Infinite loop (JSON me)
👉 Lazy loading issue

👉 Solution:
@JsonIgnore


🎯 Ultra Short Notes
OneToOne → 1-1
OneToMany → 1-many
ManyToOne → many-1
ManyToMany → many-many

